  "course_description": "Introduces first-year students to the discipline of history, particularly historical sources and methods; aims to improve critical reading, analytical, and writing skills in small group discussion.",
  "course_notes": "(Same as JS 190 2) (Freshmen Seminar - Limited to First Year Students Only) (This course will explore Jews' place in America's diverse ethnic and racial mix. We will compare the history and experiences of Jews in the U.S. to those of African Americans, Asian Americans, Latinos, and European ethnic groups, and will also consider how Jewishness has often overlapped with these other identities. In all of these cases, we will be exploring how American definitions of race and ethnicity have shaped Jewish identity, and to what extent Jews can be considered \"insiders\" or \"outsiders\" in American life.)",
